<subSubSection id="7C1A300FF0BE69675E3D43A000D89AA0" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" type="notes">
<paragraph id="9D8C20E54005566802A891C2AD9E06F5" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="70CAC38D7329F9708125447D0A4DAE50" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">
The description is largely based on DAOM 220988 due to good development of conidiomata. However, we select DAOM 230637 as the holotype, because DNA data are only available for this specimen. Microscopic data of the two specimens are identical. This species is currently only known as an asexual morph. One specimen from Victoria (DAVFP 3092) contains also an immature sexual morph, which corresponds to 
<taxonomicName id="E1DC9D43C2A5587D2EC9087EAE2A544F" authorityName="Tul. &amp; C. Tul., Select. fung. carpol. (Paris) 2: 122" authorityYear="1863" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconis alni" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="alni">
<emphasis id="97605188919E35835E9EAE569E800593" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">Melanconis alni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
superficially. Barr apparently identified her collections as 
<taxonomicName id="6B96B93402AED563EF558A25347FC78D" genus="M." lsidName="M. marginalis" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" rank="species" species="marginalis">
<emphasis id="9DC7DAB488BFAE8C63AC13A228D8D768" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">M. marginalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because the latter was, at that time, considered to be the only alnicolous species occurring in North America (
<bibRefCitation id="64CE1C328C152B62838914A341EAB97C" author="Jensen, JD" journalOrPublisher="Mycotaxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" pagination="275 - 281" refId="B21" refString="Jensen, JD, 1984. Melanconis marginalis from Northern Idaho. Mycotaxon 20: 275 - 281" title="Melanconis marginalis from Northern Idaho." volume="20" year="1984">Jensen 1984</bibRefCitation>
), which also occurs on 
<taxonomicName id="FC8AC1D4E16BBDBD178BBBB0DD617D8C" genus="A." lsidName="A. rubra" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" rank="species" species="rubra">
<emphasis id="62906291C89C213A19CC77F1B6B983BD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">A. rubra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="A73A3E0E3925764FA37BFCB73241FE36" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1139/b91-272" author="Sieber, TN" journalOrPublisher="Canadian Journal of Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" pagination="2170 - 2176" refId="B39" refString="Sieber, TN, Sieber-Canavesi, F, Petrini, O, Ekramoddoullah, AKM, Dorworth, CE, 1991. Characterization of Canadian and European Melanconium from some Alnus species by morphological, cultural and biochemical studies. Canadian Journal of Botany 69: 2170 - 2176, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1139/b91-272" title="Characterization of Canadian and European Melanconium from some Alnus species by morphological, cultural and biochemical studies." url="https://doi.org/10.1139/b91-272" volume="69" year="1991">Sieber et al. 1991</bibRefCitation>
). However, the conidia of the latter species are longer, more fusoid, have a larger l/w ratio and are lighter in colour than those of 
<taxonomicName id="6FFC28143AEFD8524CB240E5CAD91CB8" genus="M." lsidName="M. pacifica" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" rank="species" species="pacifica">
<emphasis id="9CDF2D20ECDBECDEB300E9791B80A6BC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">M. pacifica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<normalizedToken id="E53D0FFEAF413B1E2F97FE05D04B4FFD" originalValue="α-conidia">α-conidia</normalizedToken>
of 
<taxonomicName id="22613C9BB3329CCFECF4FD5B85463714" genus="M." lsidName="M. pacifica" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" rank="species" species="pacifica">
<emphasis id="F55074D49B5DC3150A39DB156DA1CD1E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">M. pacifica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="EAC904852284EC510C1F25D2C622EE1F" genus="M." lsidName="M. alni" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" rank="species" species="alni">
<emphasis id="6B4E9F80ECCF0C5BD07C23B0DF247BD5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">M. alni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are virtually identical in size. Those of the latter, however, have a different shape, a median light band and a more greyish-brown colour. Remarkably, 
<bibRefCitation id="1077DE33F85578477FA2357326A5F8A9" author="Wehmeyer, LE" journalOrPublisher="University of Michigan Studies, Scientific Series" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" pagination="1 - 161" refId="B64" refString="Wehmeyer, LE, 1941. A Revision of Melanconis, Pseudovalsa, Prosthecium, and Titania. University of Michigan Studies, Scientific Series 14: 1 - 161" title="A Revision of Melanconis, Pseudovalsa, Prosthecium, and Titania." volume="14" year="1941">Wehmeyer (1941)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned a collection from the American Pacific region (Oregon) which had conidia resembling 
<taxonomicName id="AAD8CCA27CFDD8F4BB2D9B8C9B191048" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconium sphaeroideum" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="sphaeroideum">
<emphasis id="A168F9333EAD419A0FE51F8DDEA42CE1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">Melanconium sphaeroideum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="1D50C82AC42AB4B4997B5C3D86B536D2" genus="M." lsidName="M. alni" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" rank="species" species="alni">
<emphasis id="73DCC1BD5D19588F9AA8E0C46EC7769B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">M. alni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="3CDC75B35ED577116C4E5610CF69A342" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1139/b91-272" author="Sieber, TN" journalOrPublisher="Canadian Journal of Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" pagination="2170 - 2176" refId="B39" refString="Sieber, TN, Sieber-Canavesi, F, Petrini, O, Ekramoddoullah, AKM, Dorworth, CE, 1991. Characterization of Canadian and European Melanconium from some Alnus species by morphological, cultural and biochemical studies. Canadian Journal of Botany 69: 2170 - 2176, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1139/b91-272" title="Characterization of Canadian and European Melanconium from some Alnus species by morphological, cultural and biochemical studies." url="https://doi.org/10.1139/b91-272" volume="69" year="1991">Sieber et al. (1991)</bibRefCitation>
included 10 isolates from 
<taxonomicName id="97CF111E5B36C6FBC1A908C507498D94" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Alnus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Alnus rubra" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rubra">
<emphasis id="14A2C930CD77B5121C4E32BE5945E134" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">Alnus rubra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, sampled in British Columbia, that they identified as 
<taxonomicName id="FC8A220BB7FD6A103CEA1198639DB845" authorityName="Link" authorityYear="1825" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconium apiocarpum" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="apiocarpum">
<emphasis id="DCF0D44D0003FC8CA7AB029DE80D18D9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">Melanconium apiocarpum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, another synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="457AB0567EDC476B13B2CCDEA5DB094A" genus="M." lsidName="M. alni" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" rank="species" species="alni">
<emphasis id="E16F2868C27E0E4E861DADFE3766BB38" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">M. alni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see above), based on conidial size and shape. Their measurements and, in particular, their illustration (fig. 2a) of 
<normalizedToken id="5628BDC7A7CD157EB9F2587A4B613489" originalValue="α-conidia">α-conidia</normalizedToken>
fully agree with 
<taxonomicName id="4B3D43EDFF18A5C5AC1637D373BFE073" genus="M." lsidName="M. pacifica" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" rank="species" species="pacifica">
<emphasis id="AB5937BC8069574DA4C3554752293A8E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">M. pacifica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The isozyme patterns of 
<bibRefCitation id="41E0EDE478564C64C066B3C97A084399" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1139/b91-272" author="Sieber, TN" journalOrPublisher="Canadian Journal of Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" pagination="2170 - 2176" refId="B39" refString="Sieber, TN, Sieber-Canavesi, F, Petrini, O, Ekramoddoullah, AKM, Dorworth, CE, 1991. Characterization of Canadian and European Melanconium from some Alnus species by morphological, cultural and biochemical studies. Canadian Journal of Botany 69: 2170 - 2176, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1139/b91-272" title="Characterization of Canadian and European Melanconium from some Alnus species by morphological, cultural and biochemical studies." url="https://doi.org/10.1139/b91-272" volume="69" year="1991">Sieber et al. (1991)</bibRefCitation>
revealed high similarities, but also diagnostic differences between the isolates from European 
<taxonomicName id="4EDE6DC3567D6F38690167CD9377EB3E" genus="A." lsidName="A. glutinosa" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" rank="species" species="glutinosa">
<emphasis id="8A8FE6AC6D02BD8B4FC0E15512DF004B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">A. glutinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and Canadian 
<taxonomicName id="046C521D4C8F8215D68063AADC965C56" genus="A." lsidName="A. rubra" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" rank="species" species="rubra">
<emphasis id="D178CEA4DF7675333A41AEC87C55760B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">A. rubra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is in agreement with the close phylogenetic relationship between 
<taxonomicName id="C2189D43574CDD30F0575C18DB33C861" genus="M." lsidName="M. alni" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" rank="species" species="alni">
<emphasis id="6D82F5613663529B38605E01E95B0697" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">M. alni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="66F5A9DF61435439FF749E0B1DFE2B27" genus="M." lsidName="M. pacifica" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" rank="species" species="pacifica">
<emphasis id="5AE71C3A6A45215D5870443258EDA079" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">M. pacifica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Our morphological re-investigations of the isolates of 
<bibRefCitation id="F4C6BD98C4AFCE312B9EC9D28E6F52D8" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1139/b91-272" author="Sieber, TN" journalOrPublisher="Canadian Journal of Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" pagination="2170 - 2176" refId="B39" refString="Sieber, TN, Sieber-Canavesi, F, Petrini, O, Ekramoddoullah, AKM, Dorworth, CE, 1991. Characterization of Canadian and European Melanconium from some Alnus species by morphological, cultural and biochemical studies. Canadian Journal of Botany 69: 2170 - 2176, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1139/b91-272" title="Characterization of Canadian and European Melanconium from some Alnus species by morphological, cultural and biochemical studies." url="https://doi.org/10.1139/b91-272" volume="69" year="1991">Sieber et al. (1991)</bibRefCitation>
, which are kept as dried cultures at DAVFP (see specimens cited above), confirmed that they represent 
<taxonomicName id="2ED4843CE0886DE7EB20A84759327C37" genus="M." lsidName="M. pacifica" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" rank="species" species="pacifica">
<emphasis id="D831E809479C461A65A0413F5999FE95" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">M. pacifica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E683FACF69DD1E8D280C545FF281FBF8" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">
In DAOM, two additional specimens, labelled 
<taxonomicName id="A4AE1153648E218AF2A1B94D1B50C376" authorityName="Wehm., Pap. Michigan Acad. I. 6: 382" authorityYear="1926" baseAuthorityName="Peck" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconis marginalis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="marginalis">
<emphasis id="1A031AFC6837633AF518FF888A2336CE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">Melanconis marginalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected by Barr in the same area, are extant, DAOM 227727 and DAOM 227345. These specimens, however, do not contain 
<taxonomicName id="B49359FBFCFBC0CAA8AEC5D91D9CDFE4" genus="M." lsidName="M. pacifica" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" rank="species" species="pacifica">
<emphasis id="A46A337B79DAD47284344BD0FB16CEE5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">M. pacifica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the sexual morph of a 
<taxonomicName id="84D8CE823B9CFD053FF0FEE859AD0730" authorityName="Nitschke &amp; Pyrenomyc.Germ" authorityYear="1870" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diaporthaceae" genus="Diaporthe" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Diaporthe" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6A3F00B936B78DB2E67B288D91FC1DF1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">Diaporthe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp.
</paragraph>
